Eventtia is an event management platform used by thousands of event organizers across the world to run their events inside their organizations (We just signed up Universidad de los Andes :-) as one of our clients) .  Our porpouse is allowing them to understand their data across all their events.  They have implemented a very basic solution using Metabase (https://metabase.com/) and we think we just scratched the tip of the iceberg but we lack the knowledge to go deeper and provide them with more valuable inishgts.  Every organizer has thousands of data points that we think can be processed to extract very interesting insights that can be extremely valuable when planning their next events and be used for their decision making process.​

Project title: What are the requirements for a programming course
Paragraph describing the project: Given that more than a thousand students take the Object Oriented Programming class each semester, our client wants to determine the main reasons why students fail or withdraw the class. The latter in order to identify factors that affect class performance and take preventive measures towards students, this way aiming to increase the number of successful people enrolled in the new Introduction to Programming class.

Project title: Cartographies of socio-environmental conflicts in Colombia
Paragraph describing the project: The Foundation Paz y Reconciliación (Pares) is carrying out a research agenda on socio-environmental conflicts in Colombia that, among other objectives, seeks to understand the relationship between three analytical dimensions: i. agricultural production and deforestation, ii. land concentration and iii. armed conflict in the country's territories. To contribute to this purpose, a data visualization project was carried out that allows analysts of the Foundation's Information System to investigate the possible correlations and dependencies between several of the indicators that best represent these dimensions, always offering a comparative view from the regional and the temporal.

High-cost diseases have a great social and economic impact, in large part due to the costs derived from medicines that have problems for their treatment, since access to them faces increasing difficulties and challenges, among which We find the reduced levels of coverage and financial fragility of health systems, the limitations of drug distribution networks and the general problems of access to health services for a large part of the population.

Project title: Vivo Lab - Generating value from stories using Visual Analytics
Paragraph describing the project:
Using 5000 stories from Bogotá and Medellín public midschools, we managed to create a couple of visualizations that the user can interact with, in order to extract value from the categories associated to the stories, and the stories itselves. 
There is a dynamic, orderable and interactive heatmap. Besides, there's a graph which nodes are the words the students used in their stories.
The purpose of the visualizations is to let the user to dive into the many categories that the dataset delivers, using tools as filtering, ordering and manipulating the visualizations in his/her behalf. This shall let the user find insights that can't be discovered using the data as is.
The main goal of the project is that the user can make smart choices based in the data. These choices must be directed to enhance the teachers and schools strength, to increase the edicuation level of the students.
